What is google cloud shell : 
============================
Cloud Shell allows secure, quick access to GCP resources without local setup.

1. Cloud Shell Basics :
-----------------------
  Cloud Shell = browser-based Linux VM with:
  Preinstalled gcloud, gsutil, kubectl
  Temporary (but persistent $HOME)
  Uses your logged-in GCP identity

2. Authentication & Project Setup :
-----------------------------------
  Cmd to check active account : gcloud auth list
  Cmd to check active project : gcloud config list project
  Cmd to set project (very common interview task) : gcloud config set project my-gcp-project-id

3. List Buckets :
-----------------
  List all buckets in project : gsutil ls  (gsutil ls without args lists all buckets under the active project).

4. Create Buckets :
-------------------
  Create a regional bucket : gsutil mb -p my-gcp-project-id -l asia-south1 gs://my-regional-bucket/
  Create multi-region bucket : gsutil mb -p my-gcp-project-id -l US gs://my-multiregion-bucket/
  Create bucket with storage class : gsutil mb -p my-gcp-project-id -l asia-south1 -c NEARLINE gs://my-nearline-bucket/
  Note : Location and storage class are fixed at bucket creation time.

5. Upload Objects to Bucket :
-----------------------------
   Upload single file : gsutil cp myfile.txt gs://my-regional-bucket/
   Upload directory recursively : gsutil cp -r ./logs gs://my-regional-bucket/
   List Objects Inside Bucket : gsutil ls gs://my-regional-bucket/

6. Copy Objects Between Buckets :
---------------------------------
   Copy single object (asia ‚Üí us) : gsutil cp gs://asia-bucket/data.csv gs://us-bucket/  (This creates a new copy in destination region).
   Copy entire folder across regions : gsutil cp -r gs://asia-bucket/logs gs://us-bucket/
      Is this a replication?  ‚ùå No ‚Äî this is a one-time copy.

7. Parallel copy (PRODUCTION üî•) :
----------------------------------
   gsutil -m cp -r gs://asia-bucket/logs gs://us-bucket/ [-m = multithreaded ‚Üí faster for large data]

8. Change Storage Class of Existing Objects :
---------------------------------------------
   Standard ‚Üí Coldline : gsutil rewrite -s COLDLINE gs://my-bucket/**
   Note : You cannot change bucket storage class, but you can rewrite objects.

9. Enable Versioning (Safety Feature) :
---------------------------------------
   gsutil versioning set on gs://my-regional-bucket/

10. Lifecycle Rules (REAL WORLD) : 
----------------------------------
   Example lifecycle.json :
   -------------------------
{
  "rule": [
    {
      "action": {"type": "SetStorageClass", "storageClass": "NEARLINE"},
      "condition": {"age": 30}
    },
    {
      "action": {"type": "Delete"},
      "condition": {"age": 365}
    }
  ]
}
 Apply lifecycle : [Lifecycle rules automate cost optimization]
 -----------------
   gsutil lifecycle set lifecycle.json gs://my-regional-bucket/ 

11. IAM Permissions via Command Line :
--------------------------------------
  Grant read access : gsutil iam ch user:abc@gmail.com:objectViewer gs://my-regional-bucket/
  View IAM policy : gsutil iam get gs://my-regional-bucket/

12. Storage Transfer Service (Complex Use Case) :
-------------------------------------------------
  From S3 ‚Üí GCS (Conceptual) : gcloud transfer jobs create s3://source-bucket gs://dest-bucket
  Used for:
    One-time or scheduled migration
    Large-scale enterprise transfers

 13. Prevent Accidental Deletes :
 --------------------------------
     gsutil retention set 365d gs://finance-bucket/

 14. Difference between cp and rsync?
 -------------------------------------
    cp copies everything, rsync copies only differences.

 15. How to speed up large transfers?
 ------------------------------------
    Use -m flag.
 





  
    
